title: Windows 10 Enterprise 2015 LTSB (x86) en-us
description:
FriendlyName: Windows 10 Enterprise 2015 LTSB (x86) en-us
Filename: en_windows_10_enterprise_2015_ltsb_x86_dvd_6848454.iso
Language: English
SHA1: ABE400AD86C604197A3B163E31AFCC1B7C53325E

Random Notes:
As usual, don't trust me, trust the math: check the MSDN hash.
Google "MSDN subscriber downloads" which will take you to: <a href="
https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/subscriptions/downloads/default.aspx" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/subscriptions/downloads/default.aspx</a>
Select Product Categories -> Operating Systems -> Windows 10 -> Filter by 32bit ISO's
look for Windows 10 Enterprise 2015 LTSB (x86) - DVD (English)
click on "details" and check the filename, if the filename is the same and the 
SHA1 hash on the file you downloaded doesn't match then rightclick->delete.

MS updates their images with the latest patches in "refresh" images every 
so often, and updates the service pack of the image (reflected in the filename). 
After that it becomes a bit more difficult to verify
older but still genuine MSDN downloads. If anyone knows of a site
that lists the hashes of older MSDN files please post it
in the comments.


So anyway, uploaded since since I couldn't find a good source.
Enjoy~
